commit.message:
Fix finding packages witch hatchling >= 1.19.0

Explicitly specify the package name to install, in order to fix
compatibility with `hatchling >= 1.19.0`.  Starting with this version
(though Frozen-Flask is affected since 1.20.0, due to a bug
in hatchling), it is necessary to explicitly select packages if they
do not

As of hatchling >= 1.19.0, it is necessary to explicitly specify
`packages` to use if they do not fit the default heuristics (i.e. are
disjoint from the project name).

Since the package is now specified explicitly, the `exclude` rules are
no longer necessary.

commit.message:
Fix `pyproject.toml` not to install tests as top-level package

Fix the `pyproject.toml` configuration not to install e.g.:

    /usr/lib/python3.11/site-packages/tests

Remove labels

These badges were actually only drawn on GitHub, and they’re now pretty
useless.

The latest PyPI version is the same as the latest version displayed on the
project’s home page on GitHub. The build status is now in GitHub Actions, so
it’s only one click away from the home page.

commit.message:
Pin Flask version to < 3.0

This version of Frozen-Flask is not compatible with Flask 3.x.

Update maintenance information

The AUTHORS file has been removed because its content was obsolete and is a
burden to maintain up-to-date. The list of contributors is already available on
the project’s home page on GitHub, and can be easily retrieved with Git.
Add configuration file for Read the Docs

Drop official PyPy support

Tests randomly fail, and it already was the case with v0.18.
